Kit Fine (B.A., Oxford; Ph.D., Warwick) specializes in Metaphysics, Logic, and Philosophy of Language. He is a fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences, and a corresponding fellow of the British Academy. He has held fellowships from the Guggenheim Foundation and the American Council of Learned Societies and is a former editor of the Journal of Symbolic Logic . In addition to his primary areas of research, he has written papers in ancient philosophy, linguistics, computer science, and economic theory. Kit Fine, Faculty of Philosophy | NYU                                                                                                                                                   Back to Previous Page                        Kit Fine   University Professor and Silver Professor of Philosophy and Mathematics; Professor          of           Philosophy Department of Philosophy 5 Washington Place New York, NY 10003               Phone:           (212) 998-3558             Fax:           (212) 995-4179             Email:               Office Hours: Tuesday, 3:30–4.30pm   Ph.D. 1969 (philosophy), Warwick; B.A. 1967 (philosophy), Oxford.         Kit Fine (B.A., Oxford; Ph.D., Warwick) specializes in Metaphysics, Logic, and Philosophy of Language. He is a fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences, and a corresponding fellow of the British Academy. He has held fellowships from the Guggenheim Foundation and the American Council of Learned Societies and is a former editor of the Journal of Symbolic Logic . In addition to his primary areas of research, he has written papers in ancient philosophy, linguistics, computer science, and economic theory.
